# Agent layer doctrine

Before creating or moving a file under `packages/agent/src/`, pick a layer:

| Kind of code | Put it in |
| --- | --- |
| Enums / types / tenant shapes | `domain/` (never `domain/services/`) |
| Pure decisions (plan, clarify, policy, doctrine, recover, ‚Ä¶) | `core/<cluster>/` |
| Host, run loop, delegate drivers | `runtime/` |
| I/O contracts + Audit/Learner/adapters | `ports/` |
| Executable tools | `tools/` |
| Model adapters / token budgeting | `llm/` / `memory/` |
| Logger / JSON / paths | `internal/` |

**Do not** resurrect `application/`, `concepts/`, `contracts/`, `decisions/`, or `engine/`.

**Import direction** (enforced by `npm run lint:arch`):

- `domain` ‚Üí only `domain` (debt allowlists only for known exceptions)
- `core` ‚Üí `domain`, `ports`, `tools`, `internal` ‚Äî not `runtime` (except allowlisted plan‚Üîdelegate debt)
- `runtime` ‚Üí may use core/domain/ports/tools/llm/memory/internal
- Outside the package: import `@mia/agent` only

**State:** Runtime owns state. Core is pure. Thread deps as parameters. Documented ambient exception: `getTenantConfig` / `setTenantConfig` in `domain/tenant`.

**Flat control flow** (monorepo-wide ‚Äî `first-principles.mdc`): peer handlers + explicit params/state. Never nest handler functions that `.on` / `addEventListener` from inside a hot path, or register un-cleared repeating timers. Trivial one-shot `setTimeout(() => ‚Ä¶)` is fine. Wire listeners at `create*` / `start*` / boot. Enforced by `lint:arch` (`flat-control-flow`).

**Naming:** Say **agent ports** / **agent internal** ‚Äî the same folder names exist on server and sync.

Full contract: `docs/doctrine.md`.
